  "text": "HTTP filter chain registration and execution in Envoy spans multiple components across the codebase.\n\n## Registration Phase\n\nThe HTTP filter chain registration begins with configuration in protobuf definitions. The `HttpConnectionManager` message is defined in both v3 (`envoy/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/v3/http_connection_manager.proto`) and v2 (`envoy/config/filter/network/http_connection_manager/v2/http_connection_manager.proto`) versions. These proto messages contain the `filter_chains` field that defines which HTTP filters should be applied to incoming requests.\n\nThe `FilterChainFactory` interface (in `envoy/http/filter_factory.h`) is the abstract base for creating HTTP filter chains. It defines two main methods:\n- `createFilterChain()`: Called when a new HTTP stream is created on the connection\n- `createUpgradeFilterChain()`: Called when a new upgrade stream is created\n\nThe concrete implementation of `FilterChainFactory` is provided by `HttpConnectionManagerConfig` (in `source/extensions/filters/network/http_connection_manager/config.h`). This class inherits from both `Http::FilterChainFactory` and `Http::ConnectionManagerConfig`, and it processes the protobuf configuration to build the filter chain.\n\n## Configuration Processing\n\nThe `FilterChainHelper` template class (in `source/common/http/filter_chain_helper.h`) is responsible for processing filter configurations at initialization time. It takes the `HttpFilter` messages from the proto configuration and creates `FilterFactoryCb` callbacks for each filter. The `FilterChainUtility` class (also in `filter_chain_helper.h`) provides the static method `createFilterChainForFactories()` which orchestrates the creation of the filter chain from a list of factory callbacks.\n\nThe `FilterChainManager` interface (in `envoy/http/filter_factory.h`) acts as the \"sink\" where filter factories can post their filters. The main method is `applyFilterFactoryCb()` which accepts a `FilterContext` and a `FilterFactoryCb` callback.\n\nThe `FilterFactoryCb` is a function type that takes `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks&` as a parameter. Individual filter factories return these callbacks during initialization, which are then called at stream creation time.\n\n## Execution Phase\n\nAt runtime, when a new HTTP stream is created, the `ConnectionManagerImpl` (in `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.h`) - which implements the `Network::ReadFilter` interface - triggers filter chain creation by calling `createFilterChain()` on the configured `FilterChainFactory` (HttpConnectionManagerConfig). \n\nThe `FilterManager` class (in `source/common/http/filter_manager.h`) is responsible for executing the filter chain at runtime. It maintains the state of stream filters and manages their lifecycle. The `FilterManager::createFilterChain()` method calls the factory callbacks to instantiate the actual filter objects.\n\nThe `DownstreamFilterManager` (in `source/common/http/filter_manager.h`) extends `FilterManager` with explicit handling for sending local replies to the client.\n\nThe `FilterChainFactoryCallbacks` interface (in `envoy/http/filter.h`) provides the callbacks that filter factories use to add their filters to the chain:\n- `addStreamDecoderFilter()`: Adds filters that process incoming request data\n- `addStreamEncoderFilter()`: Adds filters that process outgoing response data\n- `addStreamFilter()`: Adds bidirectional filters\n- `addAccessLogHandler()`: Adds access log handlers\n- `dispatcher()`: Provides access to the thread-local dispatcher\n\n## Complete Flow\n\n1. **Configuration Loading**: Protobuf config specifies filter_chains in HttpConnectionManager message\n2. **Initialization**: HttpConnectionManagerConfig and FilterChainHelper process the config and create FilterFactoryCb callbacks\n3. **Stream Creation**: When a new HTTP stream arrives, ConnectionManagerImpl calls HttpConnectionManagerConfig::createFilterChain()\n4. **Filter Instantiation**: FilterManager calls the FilterFactoryCb callbacks which invoke FilterChainFactoryCallbacks::addStreamDecoderFilter/Encoder/Filter()\n5. **Runtime Execution**: FilterManager orchestrates the execution of the filter chain, passing data through each filter in sequence\n\nThe key architectural pattern is the use of factory callbacks (`FilterFactoryCb`) that are created at configuration time but called at stream creation time. This allows for efficient filter instantiation with proper lifecycle management while maintaining separation between configuration and stream-specific behavior."
